<P><H1 align=center>DC220 – NEW PROPERTY DESCRIPTION</H1>
<P></P>
<P>This screen collects specific details of the characteristics of the new 
property.</P>
<P><FONT color=red>Areas shown in red text are mandatory 
and must be completed to proceed.</FONT>            </P>
<P><H3>Tenure of property: </H3>Select appropriate tenure of 
new property from drop down list provided.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Property type: </H3>Select type of new property from 
drop down list. If a ‘Flat’ is selected, you will need to complete the sections 
that ask what floor the flat is on, if it is serviced by a lift and how many 
Storeys the building that holds the flat is made up of.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Property Entirely for own use: </H3>Checks that the 
property will be used solely by the applicant(s).
<P></P>
<P><H3>Residential use only: </H3>Checks that the property is 
not used for business, letting or other non-residential purposes.
<P></P>
<P><H3>New property: </H3>Is the property newly built or 
existing.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Year built: </H3>What year the new property was built.
<P></P>
<P><H3>House builders guarantee: </H3>If the property is newly 
built, some form of guarantee may be required from the house builder for the 
building work. Select the appropriate guarantee type from the drop down list. If 
a guarantee is held, input the expiry date if known.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Building and Roof construction: </H3>Select the 
construction type of the main building and roof of the property from the drop 
down lists. The lists contain the main types of materials that are used.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Total land: </H3>If it is known how many acres of land 
the property is situated in, pick the appropriate selection from the drop down 
list.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Parking arrangements: </H3>Select from the drop down 
list what parking arrangements are in place for the property, and complete the 
next 2 questions if there are garages with the property.
<P></P>
<P><H3>. of outbuildings: </H3>Type in the number of 
outbuildings at the property, such as workshops and sheds.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Residential percentage: </H3>Input the percentage 
amount of space the property is in residential use. For example, a property that 
is a shop with living accommodation may be 50% residential, 50% commercial. 
<P></P>
